You will need Maven installed - get the zip
ttps://maven.apache.org/download.cgi.
C:\Users\joeoa\Downloads\apache-maven-3.9.6-bin\apache-maven-3.9.6
C:\Users\joeoa\Downloads\apache-maven-3.9.6-bin\apache-maven-3.9.6\bin

Navigate to "Settings" (or "Preferences" on macOS) > "Plugins".
In the "Installed" tab, search for "Jetty" in the search bar.

Go to the "Run" menu and select "Edit Configurations...".
Click the "+" button to add a new configuration, and choose "Jetty Server" from the dropdown menu.

Configure the Jetty server settings in the dialog that appears:
Name: Enter a name for your Jetty run configuration.
Jetty Server: Choose the version of Jetty you want to use (if multiple versions are available).
HTTP Port: Specify the port on which Jetty will listen for HTTP requests (e.g., 8080).
WebApp: Specify the location of your web application directory or WAR file.
You can use the project directory, or specify a different directory if your web application is located elsewhere.